<div id="review_2806009521" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2806009521" />
    <a title="Dorie  - Cats&amp;Books :)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16912659-dorie---cats-books"><img alt="Dorie  - Cats&amp;Books :)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1550077760p2/16912659.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2806009521?book_show_action=true">May 11, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dorie  - Cats&amp;Books :)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dorie  - Cats&amp;Books :)" href="/user/show/16912659-dorie---cats-books">Dorie  - Cats&amp;Books :)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16912659-dorie---cats-books?shelf=currently-listening-to">currently-listening-to</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16912659-dorie---cats-books?shelf=2019-netgalley-challenge">2019-netgalley-challenge</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16912659-dorie---cats-books?shelf=audiobook">audiobook</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2806009521" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10008492809220681090">This is my first book by Mr. Baldacci as I had heard he was quite formulaic which is not something that I care for, but I decided to give it a try.<br/><br/>The story was o.k. and I think the plot flowed along well enough but only really our main character is very well developed. I understand that this is typical for series books which I don&apos;t usually read. We are assuming we will get to know the other characters in the subsequent books.<br/><br/>What I really wasn&apos;t a fan of was the audio with only two voices, one</span>
  <span id="freeText10008492809220681090" style="display:none">This is my first book by Mr. Baldacci as I had heard he was quite formulaic which is not something that I care for, but I decided to give it a try.<br /><br />The story was o.k. and I think the plot flowed along well enough but only really our main character is very well developed. I understand that this is typical for series books which I don't usually read. We are assuming we will get to know the other characters in the subsequent books.<br /><br />What I really wasn't a fan of was the audio with only two voices, one for the females and one for the males. I know that this is the way it was written and I think it would work better in a physical read where you could imagine their voices. The whole "Then Decker said . . . . . ., then Bogart said, . . . "then she answered" format was a bit confusing in the beginning, because the voice was used for several male characters it was a bit hard to keep everyone straight. <br /><br />All in all it was a good read with some very serious subjects touched upon, murder, rape, terrorism, hermaphroditism and other sexual and mental abnormalities and there are some graphically violent sections of the book.<br /><br />Read this through Overdrive from my public library!</span>
  <a data-text-id="10008492809220681090" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


