  <span id="freeText11426698131043903320" style="display:none">This book was so entertaining! I actually went ahead and put the rest of the series and also the Will Robie series on hold at my library to pick up tomorrow. I was so into this book that last night I didn’t want to stop reading to go to bed, but had to. I could not predict the way this book would unfold, which I love in mysteries. Amos Decker is an intriguing character with a great supporting cast. I hope this series continues to be as interesting as this first book. So cannot wait to go get to the library to get the other books and another Baldacci series!<br /><br />My quick and simple overall: loved this book. It was intriguing and not predictable like so many other mysteries and thrillers. <br /></span>
